Editor’s note: This live event has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - National Poet Laureate, Professor Keorapetse "Bra Willie" Kgositsile, was buried on Tuesday. The service was held at the Marks Park Sports Club in Emmerentia, Johannesburg.
	
	President Jacob Zuma has awarded the poet and activist a special official funeral and Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the eulogy. READ: A tribute to Keorapetse Kgositsile, South Africa's only poet laureate Kgositsile died nearly two weeks ago at the age of 79. He was a recipient of the National Order of Ikamanga and was installed as the country’s second National Poet Laureate in 2006. Several memorial services have been held in his honour since his death. eNCA